post: {'type': 'pro', 'text': "In a truly free society self regulation should be our privilege. You are free to not use drugs, and you should be just as free to use them. That's why all drugs should be legal."}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'Something being illegal makes the entire area "tainted." Talking about how to do something illegal is seen as encouraging said activity, and "sending the wrong signals."'}

{'type': 'con', 'text': "This doesn't necessarily mean drugs should be legalized. Alternatively, we could make alcohol, cigarettes and fast food illegal. I believe legalization of drugs is a really bad idea."}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'Criminals will face competition from legal growers with lower shipping costs, which will drive prices down.'}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'Marijuana use in the Netherlands has [not increased](https://www.opensocietyfoundations.org/voices/safe-and-effective-drug-policy-look-dutch) following decriminalisation; in fact, cannabis consumption is lower compared to countries with stricter legislation such as the UK.'}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': "Governments manipulate citizens by spreading biased information about drugs and thereby interfering with their choices. That's why legalization of drugs is a pretty good idea."}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'Legalization will help drive down the profits of drug cartels since people could get their drugs from legal reliable sources. Hence it may force the cartels to offer a purer product or less expensive to remain competitive. I believe all drugs should be legal.'}
{'type': 'con', 'text': 'Drug use correlates with criminality, thievery, and risky sexual behavior. Responsibility is a state that is easily bypassed when you enter the flow of the drug world.'}
{'type': 'con', 'text': 'This is biased against those with mental illness. So legalization of drugs is a really bad idea.'}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': '[The Controlled Substances Act](https://www.dea.gov/druginfo/ds.shtml), prohibits Schedule 1 substances \\(such as Cannabis\\), which forces patients to either break the law or use more harmful/addictive substances that are inferior medicine. So legalization of drugs is a pretty good idea.'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'Legalization reduces the danger of overdosing.'}

{'type': 'con', 'text': 'Some drugs will lead to people having hallucinations or becoming violent. In these instances, individuals may be a danger to themselves or others. I believe drugs should remain illegal.'}
{'type': 'con', 'text': 'Drugs can be used to abuse others or commit crimes.'}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': '[Sleep deprivation](https://www.sciencedaily.com/releases/2007/03/070301081831.htm) negatively affects moral judgment and decision-making. I believe all drugs should be legal.'}
{'type': 'con', 'text': 'One solution for recreational availability of such drugs could be to require that they emit an unmistakable coloring or odour/taste when dissolved in a drink.'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'Legalization will help contain the dangerous drug cartels. So all drugs should be legal.'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'Just because there are other systematic racial issues does not mean we cannot challenge this particular racist law.'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'Assuming that drugs will still be legally forbidden for people under a certain age, the distribution points will not be allowed to sell it to children.'}
{'type': 'con', 'text': 'Science can already study drugs, just with some [constraints](https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pmc/articles/PMC4307971/). I think legalization of drugs is a really bad idea.'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'This is undeniable; however, the same is true whether drugs are legal or not. I believe legalization of drugs is a pretty good idea.'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'Legalising drugs related to date rape could bring the issue further into the public eye, allowing for more widespread education on the topic.'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'The human body is very complex; a given drug can have quite subtle aspects. I believe all drugs should be legal.'}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'Through education, heavy advertising campaigns and controlling the packaging of tobacco, the government can make its negative effects clear despite it being legal. So legalization of drugs is a pretty good idea.'}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'Legalizing something means including it the current system of business oversight and regulation as other legal activities. This means documenting purchases and monetary transactions, as well as filing and paying taxes. This means more control over where drugs come from and money goes, rather than would be the case under prohibition or decriminalization.'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'Other factors contribute to the opioid crisis significantly more than the legality of currently prescribed opioids. So all drugs should be legal.'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'Information about the content of legalized drugs would be easier to find and accurate which would help people make informed and safer choice.'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': "Taking a more effective approach is not giving up. That's why legalization of drugs is a pretty good idea."}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'Legalization will allow governments to fight addictive drugs more effectively. So legalization of drugs is a pretty good idea.'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'Many constitutions and legal frameworks promote personal autonomy. I think all drugs should be legal.'}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': "The black market businesses won't be able to invest in productivity-increasing \\(especially immovable\\) capital, as the threat of being caught discourages such investments. That's why all drugs should be legal."}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': "Some people may become psychologically stressed about a friend/relative coming out as gay, or an atheist as well. That doesn't mean the friend/relative did anything wrong. I believe legalization of drugs is a pretty good idea."}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'Professional addiction treatment is usually [expensive](https://www.addictioncenter.com/rehab-questions/cost-of-drug-and-alcohol-treatment/). I believe all drugs should be legal.'}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'Ending the war on drugs will reduce [police casualties](https://www.vox.com/2014/10/29/7083371/swat-no-knock-raids-police-killed-civilians-dangerous-work-drugs). I think legalization of drugs is a pretty good idea.'}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'That correlation is not affected by their legality. So, legalization will not make it worse unless it causes the price to go down. Given the emphasis many put on drug taxes as an argument in favor of legalization, that seems unlikely.'}
{'type': 'con', 'text': "Addiction treatment isn't actually very expensive or costly, and is likely to be clinically simpler to resolve than is widely assumed."}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'The drug industry, like alcohol and tobacco, can be heavily taxed, generating high revenues. I think legalization of drugs is a pretty good idea.'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'It is better to educate people on how to use valuable-yet-dangerous things safely than to ban their use entirely.'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'Drug prohibition consumes a considerable portion of public spending.'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'Governments invested a lot of money trying to cease drug use by everyone. It failed miserably. Not only it is not the most efficient way, but it is not even achievable.'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'Since everything is legal, users can instead choose the drugs with the most benefits and the least harms.'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': "Shooting \\(illegally obtained\\) heroin is like playing Russian roulette every time: if a batch is too strong, over-dosing is likely. That's why all drugs should be legal."}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': "Reducing the number of users and frequency of use is just a means to an end. The end goal is to reduce harms created by drug use. It's perfectly possible to increase use and have less overall harm. So all drugs should be legal."}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'According to [Human Right Watch](https://www.hrw.org/news/2013/06/04/americas-decriminalize-personal-use-drugs), subjecting people to disproportionate criminal sanctions for the personal use of drugs "infringes on their autonomy".'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'Drug use will not cease regardless of the legal status. I think all drugs should be legal.'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'Heroin and other opiates cause [negligible](https://rationalwiki.org/wiki/Heroin#Health_effects) direct physical harm to the body. I think all drugs should be legal.'}
{'type': 'con', 'text': 'Legalization runs the danger of increased drug use that could impair people from doing jobs safely, making work places more dangerous.'}
{'type': 'con', 'text': 'In some instances, drug use has increased following legalisation. I believe legalization of drugs is a really bad idea.'}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'Sobriety may be required for the optimal exercise of rational moral agency; however, it is not required for the generell exercise of rational moral agency. So legalization of drugs is a pretty good idea.'}
{'type': 'con', 'text': "It can also cause users to mix alcohol with other drugs, which [endangers users' health](https://www.northpointwashington.com/blog/dangers-mixing-alcohol-drugs/) even more."}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'This is not mutually exclusive with legalizing drugs. Both could be done. I think all drugs should be legal.'}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'It is possible that decriminalization dissuades those who specifically start using drugs as a way of breaking the law, such as [early data from Portugal](https://www.leafly.com/news/politics/portugal-drug-decriminalization-statistics) suggests. I think all drugs should be legal.'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'Drugs may also alter the strength of which learning \\(permanent changes of neural activity\\) reacts to such rewards.'}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': '[Alcohol](https://theconversation.com/alcohol-leads-to-more-violence-than-other-drugs-but-youd-never-know-from-the-headlines-72281) is responsible for more violence and harm than any other drug.'}

{'type': 'con', 'text': 'If drugs are legalised, they will not be as expensive as they are now. Estimations of tax revenue based on current prices may be inaccurate. I believe drugs should remain illegal.'}
{'type': 'con', 'text': 'This is an appeal to nature fallacy. Nature is not the word on what ought to be done with its products.'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'Using a fake ID in a legal establishment implies much more work and risk than just buying from the unregulated black market.'}

{'type': 'con', 'text': 'An overdose of heroin is usually fatal without medical help; [during 2016](https://www.cdc.gov/drugoverdose/data/heroin.html), almost 15,500 people died from drug overdoses involving heroin in the United States.'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'The effects of smoking are slow and not always visible; this means people are not as aware of them.'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'Criminals will have to either adapt or lose the income that prevents their other crimes from catching up with them.'}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': "There's no reasonable way for folks to measure whether or not a drug-induced hallucinatory episode will become a violent episode any more than there's a way to determine whether someone is an angry or violent drunk. Instead the police simply deal with the drunkards after the fact rather than taking away alcohol from everyone."}

{'type': 'con', 'text': 'Drug cartels will not cease their activities if drugs are legalised. They will simply move to other areas to keep their profits \\(drugs for children, black market drugs, human trafficking\\). So drugs should remain illegal.'}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'In the US, as of 2018 there are roughly [235,000](https://www.prisonpolicy.org/reports/pie2018.html) inmates behind bars for drug-related crimes. I think legalization of drugs is a pretty good idea.'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'The legalisation of drugs could lead to better education on how to be safe around them. I think legalization of drugs is a pretty good idea.'}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'The [majority](http://www.independent.co.uk/news/habits-most-drug-users-are-happy-successful-people-with-a-taste-for-the-good-life-1292155.html) of young individuals consuming illegal substances lead fulfilling and successful lives.'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'If legalized, users could be required to carry safe containers for syringes.'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'Established companies would be strictly controlled.'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': "Regulations that prohibit working under the influence of alcohol can trivially be expanded to include all drugs. That's why all drugs should be legal."}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'A victim of such an act would not fear prosecution for consumption if drugs were legal, and therefore would more easily seek and obtain help and/or retribution.'}

{'type': 'con', 'text': 'There are still many other ways in which criminal associations could take advantage of the situation and legally start selling drugs or exploiting the farmers as they do now.'}
{'type': 'con', 'text': 'Legalizing drugs would increase the probability of violence and offenses.'}
{'type': 'con', 'text': 'The legalisation of drugs may lead to children trying and becoming involved with drugs at a younger age.'}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': "Research shows that education has helped the [decrease](https://www.huffingtonpost.com/2015/03/26/cigarette-smoking-decline_n_6855468.html) in number of tobacco smokers. That's why legalization of drugs is a pretty good idea."}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'Drug legalisation would mean governments get to suggest a recommended dose, preventing the incidence of death by overdose. I believe legalization of drugs is a pretty good idea.'}

{'type': 'con', 'text': 'The use of [drugs](https://www.academia.edu/34757965/Why_Recreational_Drug_Use_is_Immoral) that can impair the ability to make moral judgments based on clear, rational \\(and autonomous\\) thinking is immoral.'}
